text: Can someone please help with a quick session for EMAIL NURTURING? Best practices, your learnings, etc.

elements.text: Can someone please help with a quick session for EMAIL NURTURING? Best practices, your learnings, etc.

text:
1. Provide Value before asking anything
2. Keep your Email Domain clean - SPF, DKIM, DMARC
3. Keep your Email clean - minimal HTML
4. Keep cleaning your DB 
5. Separate unengaged and engaged contacts with scoring
6. Analyse performance over weeks (not days) for SaaS
7. Dont worry too much about ToFU to BoFU flow - worry about Open, CTR. Abuse initially. Once you have your audience’s attention then worry about the flow
8. Use tools (Glock Apps) to measure Inbox placement 
9. *Keep your email domain different from your main domain*

text:
A friend who worked with a popular now-dead WordPress social sharing plugin said that they figured out a model - by seeing 4 urls loaded from your browser, they can pretty accurately predict which websites you would find interesting. Their data was apparently bought by the likes of big G and Fb.  They definitely buy data, doubt if they would sell.

And any chrome/firefox plugin can pretty much see all your browsing history and track what you type. Also, Grammarly sells your data (heard from a similarweb employee)
